(r,0)
r>0
(x-r)^2 + y^2 = r^2
y>0
y
x
y(x) = \sqrt{2rx-x^2}
0 < x < 2r
x
x
A = 2\pi \int_{x_1}^{x_2} y\sqrt{1+(y')^2} \, \mathrm{d}x
x_1=0
x_2=h \le 2r
\begin{eqnarray*} A &=& 2\pi \int_0^h \sqrt{2rx-x^2}\sqrt{1+\frac{(r-x)^2}{2rx-x^2}} \, \mathrm{d}x \\ \\ \\ &=&2\pi\int_0^h \sqrt{2rx-x^2}\sqrt{\frac{r^2}{2rx-x^2}} \, \mathrm{d}x \\ \\ \\ &=&2\pi\int_0^h r\, \mathrm{d}x \\ \\ \\ &=&2\pi r h \end{eqnarray*}
\sqrt{2rh}
\pi(\sqrt{2rh})^2=2\pi rh
